Command `python3 - << 'PY'
# Performance micro-benchmark for large N,Q
import random, time
from subprocess import Popen, PIPE

n = 200000
q = 200000
s = ''.join(random.choice('01') for _ in range(n))
queries = []
for _ in range(q):
    t = random.choice([1,2])
    l = random.randint(1,n)
    r = random.randint(l,n)
    queries.append((t,l,r))

# build input
inp = []
inp.append(f"{n} {q}")
inp.append(s)
for qu in queries:
    inp.append("{} {} {}".format(*qu))
input_data = '\n'.join(inp)

p = Popen(['python3','/workspace/solution.py'], stdin=PIPE, stdout=PIPE, stderr=PIPE, text=True)
start = time.time()
out, err = p.communicate(input_data)
end = time.time()
print('Elapsed:', end-start)

inp = []

for qu in queries:
    inp.append("{} {} {}".format(*qu))
